// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance MotorShaftEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Position encoder mounted directly on the motor shaft of the MABI MAX 100 robot's first vertical axis, providing precise positional feedback for control and monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorShaftEncoderDataTransmitted
]

instance GearboxSecondaryEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Secondary position encoder positioned behind the gearbox of the MABI MAX 100 robot's first vertical axis, providing redundant positional feedback for control and monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:producedData GearboxEncoderDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance MotorShaftEncoderDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "One-way automated data flow from the motor shaft encoder to the digital shadow, containing high-precision positional data for friction modeling."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorShaftEncoder
]

instance GearboxEncoderDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "One-way automated data flow from the gearbox secondary encoder to the digital shadow, providing redundant positional data for control validation."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GearboxSecondaryEncoder
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance SysMLGeometricModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Geometric representation of the MABI MAX 100 robot's first vertical axis using SysML Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs), focusing on component interfaces and interconnections."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLToolchain, MontiArcFramework
]

instance SysMLBehavioralModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Behavioral model of the robot axis using SysML state machines (v1.7) for control logic and state transitions."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLToolchain
]

instance PhysicsBasedFrictionModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Physics-based analytical model for friction dynamics within the gearbox, derived from domain-specific simulations."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkIntegration, CppImplementation
]

instance RealTimePositionalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Aggregated real-time positional data from both encoders, preprocessed for friction analysis and control calibration."
    DTDFVocab:fromData MotorShaftEncoderDataTransmitted, GearboxEncoderDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkIntegration
]

instance HistoricalOperationalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Historical operational traces of the robot axis, including torque, velocity, and positional data for long-term friction pattern analysis."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AssetAdministrationShell
]

// C11: Enablers
instance SysMLToolchain : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "SysML-based modeling environment for system architecture and behavioral descriptions, supporting RFLP methodology."
    DTDFVocab:enables SysMLModelingService, StateMachineSimulationService
]

instance SimulinkIntegration : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MathWorks Simulink integration for dynamic system modeling, control algorithm development, and co-simulation with physical data."
    DTDFVocab:enables ControlAlgorithmService, FrictionAnalysisService
]

instance MQTTDataStream : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MQTT-based real-time data streaming protocol for one-way transmission of sensor readings and actuator commands from physical to digital."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataAcquisitionService
]

instance MontiArcFramework : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MontiArc architecture description framework for component-connector modeling and behavioral automation."
    DTDFVocab:enables ComponentIntegrationService
]

instance AssetAdministrationShell : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Standardized digital representation framework for metadata management and interoperability with industrial IoT ecosystems."
    DTDFVocab:enables DigitalShadowService
]

instance CppImplementation : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "C++ implementation framework for low-level control logic and hardware interface integration."
    DTDFVocab:enables ControlAlgorithmService
]

// C6: Services
instance DataAcquisitionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service responsible for collecting and transmitting real-time positional data from encoders via MQTT protocol."
    DTDFVocab:provides PositionalDataInsight
]

instance ControlAlgorithmService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for developing and executing control algorithms using Simulink and C++ implementations, calibrated with friction models."
    DTDFVocab:provides ControlOptimizationAction
]

instance FrictionAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for analyzing friction dynamics in the gearbox using physics-based models and historical operational data."
    DTDFVocab:provides FrictionPatternInsight
]

instance SysMLModelingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for creating and maintaining SysML-based system architecture models across multiple abstraction layers."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemArchitectureInsight
]

instance StateMachineSimulationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for simulating and validating behavioral models using SysML state machines."
    DTDFVocab:provides BehavioralValidationInsight
]

instance ComponentIntegrationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service for integrating components using MontiArc framework, ensuring proper interconnections and interfaces."
    DTDFVocab:provides ComponentIntegrationInsight
]

instance DigitalShadowService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service managing the digital shadow of the robot axis, including data aggregation and contextual abstraction."
    DTDFVocab:provides DigitalShadowInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance PositionalDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "High-precision positional data insights derived from encoder readings, used for control accuracy validation."
]

instance FrictionPatternInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identified friction patterns and anomalies within the gearbox, enabling predictive maintenance recommendations."
]

instance SystemArchitectureInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structural and behavioral insights of the robot axis derived from SysML models, supporting system evolution."
]

instance BehavioralValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation results of control logic and state transitions through state machine simulations."
]

instance ComponentIntegrationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Verification of component interconnections and interface compatibility within the MontiArc framework."
]

instance DigitalShadowInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Status and consistency of the digital shadow representation, including data synchronization metrics."
]

instance ControlOptimizationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automatic adjustment of control parameters based on friction model analysis and real-time data."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "PMSM driving the first vertical axis of the MABI MAX 100 robot, interfacing with the gearbox and encoders for precise motion control."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system emphasizes **fidelity and validity** through **comparative analysis of simulated and measured data**, where deviations between these datasets are quantified to assess model accuracy. Validation processes are implicitly tied to **semantic support mechanisms**, ensuring that aggregated data traces (from the Digital Shadow Reference Model) are correctly linked to their corresponding computational models. While explicit validation methodologies (e.g., model consistency checks, behavioral validation protocols) are not detailed, the system’s design prioritizes **data-driven model refinement** to minimize discrepancies. Uncertainty sources are implicitly addressed by the **one-way data flow** from physical to digital, where passive data collection (via Digital Shadow) is complemented by active processing in the Digital Twin to interpret and act upon deviations. No explicit error detection/correction mechanisms or formal quality assurance processes (e.g., ISO standards, statistical validation) are described in the provided documents."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system adheres to **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) standards**, including **SysML (Systems Modeling Language)** for system architecture and behavior modeling. **Architecture Description Languages (ADLs)** such as **ACME**, **AADL**, **MontiArc**, and **SysML IBDs** provide standardized frameworks for component-based system design, ensuring interoperability and modularity. The system leverages **interoperability standards** implicit in MBSE methodologies, enabling integration across **heterogeneous modeling tools** (e.g., **MathWorks Simulink**, **C++/Java-based simulations**). While no explicit **industry-specific standards** (e.g., ISO, IEC, or domain-specific certifications) are mentioned, the use of **SysML** and **ADLs** aligns with broader **systems engineering standardization efforts**. **Compliance frameworks** are not detailed, but the structured approach ensures adherence to **modeling best practices** and **toolchain interoperability** as defined by MBSE standards."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system for the MABI MAX 100 serial robot incorporates **safety-critical system considerations** through the integration of a **safety cell** that restricts the operational range of the first vertical axis to **[-90°, 90°]**, ensuring compliance with physical workspace constraints. **Fail-safe mechanisms** are implicitly addressed via the **Siemens SINUMERIK 840D sl CNC controller**, which enforces **maximum speed limits** (|q̇_max| = 75°/s) and **positional accuracy** (0.1 mm) through closed-loop control. The **dual encoder system** (motor encoder + secondary encoder behind the gearbox) mitigates **backlash and positional uncertainty** by cross-referencing encoder readings to infer **elasticity and friction** in the drive train, thereby enhancing **mechanical safety** and **operational reliability**. However, explicit **cybersecurity protocols**, **access control mechanisms**, or **threat mitigation strategies** are not detailed in the provided documents."
]